Here the challenge was to get the camera low enough to get @shaboozey within the frame and since we couldn’t dig a hole, a mirror seemed to be the best option. Originally they wanted a 35mm 2 shot from a distance but came up with this idea once I saw this random mirror on the wall. I took the frame off and there we went. Vfx by @sinzterz

As I turn to page 31 in this book of life, I am reminded of the journey I've traversed, a journey filled with challenges, triumphs, and the unwavering determination to prove myself to the world.

On this page, I pause and reflect upon those who once doubted me, those who questioned my abilities and foresaw a future devoid of success. In the face of skepticism, I made a conscious decision not to be defined by their doubts, but rather to use them as stepping stones towards my aspirations.

Each skeptical whisper and every disbelieving gaze became the fuel that ignited my inner fire. I took those doubts and transformed them into motivation, channeling their negative energy into positive actions. With persistence and dedication, I embarked on a path of self-improvement, growth, and learning.
